abstract: Tide Pod shout-outs onscreen. Flirtatious exchanges with companies on Twitter. Netflix may not run ads, but it has become a coveted marketing platform.
snippet: Tide Pod shout-outs onscreen. Flirtatious exchanges with companies on Twitter. Netflix may not run ads, but it has become a coveted marketing platform.
lead_paragraph: Netflix subscribers like being able to glide through entire seasons of “Stranger Things” and “The Crown” without sitting through commercials for insurance and S.U.V.s with bows on the hood. Subscriptions, rather than advertising, drive its nearly $16 billion in annual revenue, and being commercial-free “remains a deep part of our brand proposition,” Netflix said in a statement.

abstract: His best-known book, “Frindle,” posed a question about the nature of words: What would happen if you called a pen a frindle?
snippet: His best-known book, “Frindle,” posed a question about the nature of words: What would happen if you called a pen a frindle?
lead_paragraph: Andrew Clements, who mined a brief teaching career in Illinois in writing two dozen books for young readers, most notably “Frindle,” which sold more than eight million copies, died on Nov. 28 at his home in West Baldwin, Maine. He was 70.

abstract: In the first nominating state, many Democrats feel a responsibility to identify a candidate who can win in states more diverse than their own.
snippet: In the first nominating state, many Democrats feel a responsibility to identify a candidate who can win in states more diverse than their own.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Iowa — They share awkward glances at events where nearly everyone looks like them. They take comfort in reminding one another that they propelled Barack Obama to the White House. They swear that their values and priorities are representative of more than a Corn Belt farm state.

abstract: Chinese Embassy officials trespassed onto a Virginia base that is home to Special Operations forces. Their expulsions added to tensions between Washington and Beijing.
snippet: Chinese Embassy officials trespassed onto a Virginia base that is home to Special Operations forces. Their expulsions added to tensions between Washington and Beijing.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The American government secretly expelled two Chinese Embassy officials this fall after they drove on to a sensitive military base in Virginia, according to people with knowledge of the episode. The expulsions appear to be the first of Chinese diplomats suspected of espionage in more than 30 years.

lead_paragraph: SUNDAY PUZZLE — This beautiful grid was a slow burner exemplified. If you’re here in search of answers and explanations, the whole thing didn’t click for me until it was complete, so I’m with you. You will be delighted to unravel all of the strands, which we will do here together; it’s well worth it.

abstract: Nine presidential candidates have signed a letter urging the D.N.C. to adjust its qualification criteria for January and February.
snippet: Nine presidential candidates have signed a letter urging the D.N.C. to adjust its qualification criteria for January and February.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — At the urging of Senator Cory Booker of New Jersey, eight Democratic presidential candidates, and Mr. Booker, have signed a letter urging Tom Perez, the Democratic National Committee chairman, to lower the thresholds to qualify for the party’s January and February debates.
